#. type: Title ==
#: _guides/agent-mcp.adoc
msgid "Documentation search with RAG"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _guides/agent-mcp.adoc
msgid ""
"The Agent MCP server includes a semantic search capability powered by a Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) system.\n"
"This allows AI coding agents to search Quarkus documentation intelligently and get relevant answers to questions."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: _guides/agent-mcp.adoc
msgid "How it works"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _guides/agent-mcp.adoc
msgid "The documentation RAG system:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _guides/agent-mcp.adoc
msgid "**Indexes Quarkus documentation** — On first use, the server downloads and indexes the official Quarkus documentation for the version matching your project (or the latest version if no project is specified)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _guides/agent-mcp.adoc
msgid "**Creates embeddings** — Documentation is chunked and converted into vector embeddings for semantic search"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _guides/agent-mcp.adoc
msgid "**Semantic retrieval** — When an AI agent searches for documentation, the system finds the most relevant chunks based on semantic similarity, not just keyword matching"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _guides/agent-mcp.adoc
msgid "**Version-aware** — Documentation matches your project's Quarkus version, ensuring accuracy"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: _guides/agent-mcp.adoc
msgid "Usage"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _guides/agent-mcp.adoc
msgid ""
"AI coding agents can search documentation by querying the Quarkus Agent MCP server.\n"
"For example, searching for \"how to configure datasource\" will return relevant documentation chunks about datasource configuration, even if those exact words don't appear in the documentation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _guides/agent-mcp.adoc
msgid ""
"The RAG system is automatically initialized on the first documentation search.\n"
"The initial indexing may take a moment, but subsequent searches are fast."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: _guides/agent-mcp.adoc
msgid "Extension documentation RAG"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _guides/agent-mcp.adoc
msgid ""
"In addition to the main Quarkus documentation, the RAG system also includes extension-specific documentation from the extension modules.\n"
"Each extension can contribute its own documentation, which is automatically discovered and indexed alongside the core documentation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _guides/agent-mcp.adoc
msgid "This ensures that when working with an extension, AI agents have access to:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _guides/agent-mcp.adoc
msgid "Extension-specific configuration options"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _guides/agent-mcp.adoc
msgid "API usage patterns"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _guides/agent-mcp.adoc
msgid "Integration examples"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _guides/agent-mcp.adoc
msgid "Troubleshooting guides"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _guides/agent-mcp.adoc
msgid "The extension documentation is pulled from the extension's runtime module and is version-matched to your project, ensuring consistency between the code and documentation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _guides/agent-mcp.adoc
msgid "Extension skills"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _guides/agent-mcp.adoc
msgid ""
"Extensions can provide AI coding agents with extension-specific coding guidelines, testing patterns, and common pitfalls by shipping a `quarkus-skill.md` file.\n"
"During the Quarkus build, all skill files are automatically discovered, composed with extension metadata (name, description, guide URL, categories), and aggregated into a single `io.quarkus:quarkus-extension-skills` JAR following the https://agentskills.io/specification[Agent Skills specification].\n"
"This JAR is published to Maven Central with each Quarkus release and is compatible with https://www.skillsjars.com[SkillsJars]."
msgstr ""

