#. type: Plain text
#: _guides/agent-mcp.adoc
msgid "The Quarkus build automatically discovers all `quarkus-skill.md` files across all extensions and aggregates them into the `quarkus-extension-skills` artifact."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _guides/agent-mcp.adoc
msgid ""
"If your extension's runtime module has a `description` field in `META-INF/quarkus-extension.yaml`, it will be included in the composed skill's YAML frontmatter to help AI agents discover and understand your extension.\n"
"The `categories` field under `metadata` is also included, allowing AI agents to group skills by category.\n"
"While optional, providing a description and categories is recommended:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _guides/agent-mcp.adoc
msgid ""
"The file should contain concise, actionable Markdown content.\n"
"Focus on what an AI agent needs to know to use your extension correctly:"
